# Simulation directory boundary

## Role

- **`#features/simulation`** — org-scoped **operational simulation**: registered scenario graphs, replay into real `onething` + `iam_audit_event` rows, clear-by-run, Server Actions behind **`AFENDA_ENABLE_SIMULATION=1`** (`OPERATIONAL_SIMULATION_ENV`).
- **`#lib/erp/simulation-context.server.ts`** — **`AsyncLocalStorage`** context consumed by **`writeIamAuditEvent`** and OneThing inserts so simulation provenance stamps consistently.
- **`#lib/erp/scenario-types.shared.ts`** — **`scenarioIdSchema`** and replay input shapes (client/CLI-safe).

## Imports

- Routes and scripts: **`#features/simulation`**, **`#features/simulation/server`**, **`#features/simulation/client`** (client islands); do not deep-import `#features/simulation/data/...` from outside the module.
- IAM audit provenance constants: **`#lib/auth`** (`AUDIT_ORIGIN`, `AUDIT_ACTOR_MODE`).

## Forbidden

- Enabling replay/clear in production without explicit env (**never default `AFENDA_ENABLE_SIMULATION`**).
- Bypassing **`deleteOperationalSimulationRun`** predicates (`audit_origin`, `simulation_run_id`) for bulk deletes.
- New scenario IDs that do not pass **`scenarioIdSchema`**.

## Contract

- New scenarios: register in **`data/scenario-registry.server.ts`**, add graph under **`data/scenario-graphs/`**, extend **`AGENTS.md`** IAM examples if new audit actions are introduced.
